33:42.754 --> 33:46.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Kate and baby
Caroline are
part of an ongoing research
effort out of

33:46.724 --> 33:52.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Columbia University Medical
Center and New
York Presbyterian examining
whether the most

33:52.397 --> 33:58.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
basic nurturing techniques, like
this quiet
moment, can help heal the
traumas of premature

33:58.336 --> 33:59.670 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
birth.

33:59.704 --> 34:03.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: The more you do this, the
more you
reinforce that connection.

34:03.107 --> 34:05.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATE ILIE: It took us a little
while, but
we're doing it now.

34:05.410 --> 34:07.178 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

34:07.211 --> 34:11.249 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARTHA WELCH, Columbia
University: You are
calming me, and I am calming
you, and then

34:11.282 --> 34:14.185 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the two crave being together,
and it's self-perpetuating.

34:14.218 --> 34:18.289 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: This
intervention is the
brainchild of Dr. Martha Welch.

34:18.322 --> 34:22.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She says that, while much of
this seems like
the standard care offered to
premature babies

34:22.760 --> 34:29.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and their parents, here, the
focus is 100
percent on strengthening the
emotional connection

34:29.200 --> 34:30.334 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
between mother and child.

34:30.368 --> 34:31.335 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

34:31.369 --> 34:32.403 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARTHA WELCH: It's not cerebral.

34:32.437 --> 34:33.471 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's visceral.

34:33.504 --> 34:35.106 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's gut feelings.

34:35.139 --> 34:39.744 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they're beginning to set
this pattern
of calming each other.

34:39.777 --> 34:41.446 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: It seems so
basic.

34:41.479 --> 34:42.447 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

34:42.480 --> 34:44.282 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARTHA WELCH: Very basic.

34:44.315 --> 34:48.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: For the last
few months,
we have been following several
moms and their

34:48.119 --> 34:51.322 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
premature babies through this
process.

34:51.355 --> 34:56.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Neonatal intensive care units
give these children
a better shot at survival now
than at any

34:56.327 --> 34:58.262 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
other time in history.

34:58.296 --> 35:04.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
