35:06.871 --> 35:13.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, despite that, leaving the
womb so early
still puts these kids at high
risk for emotional,

35:13.177 --> 35:15.713 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
behavioral and developmental
challenges.

35:15.746 --> 35:18.616 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This intervention is meant to
help minimize
those impacts.

35:18.649 --> 35:21.319 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: You make momma feel more
comfortable
now.

35:21.352 --> 35:25.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Nurse Mary
McKiernan says
step one is often connecting
with a child

35:25.823 --> 35:29.260 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that's literally wrapped in
lifesaving technology.

35:29.293 --> 35:31.062 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They call these calming
Sessions.

35:31.095 --> 35:34.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARY MCKIERNAN, Nurse: There's
so much medical
equipment, and monitors, and
beeping, and

35:34.999 --> 35:35.967 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
some mothers, they're afraid.

35:36.000 --> 35:37.935 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're afraid to speak to their
babies.

35:37.969 --> 35:41.139 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATE ILIE: I'm trying to figure
out how to
hold Caroline.

35:41.172 --> 35:42.440 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She has her CPAP on.

35:42.473 --> 35:44.542 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
