your baby?"

35:53.384 --> 35:55.853 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I could cry just telling
this.

35:55.887 --> 35:58.122 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So I was like, I will take
anything.

35:58.156 --> 36:03.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARY MCKIERNAN: I know she's
sleeping, but
she can -- she knows your voice,
so talk to

36:03.261 --> 36:06.564 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
her in your emotional tone, as
you always
do.

36:06.597 --> 36:08.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KATE ILIE: You have had a long
morning.

36:08.399 --> 36:09.634 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You finished your whole bottle

36:09.667 --> 36:12.203 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARY MCKIERNAN: It feels good,
right?

36:12.236 --> 36:14.338 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KATE ILIE: There's nothing
better.

36:14.372 --> 36:15.606 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MARY MCKIERNAN: Yes.

36:15.640 --> 36:19.010 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KATE ILIE: It's like therapy for
both of us.

36:19.043 --> 36:25.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm telling you, that was the
first time I
felt like I could breathe, and I
could bond

36:25.583 --> 36:26.551 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with my baby.

36:26.584 --> 36:27.552 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: For the first
time?

36:27.585 --> 36:28.586 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
KATE ILIE: Yes.

36:28.619 --> 36:30.454 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And it was so emotional.

36:30.488 --> 36:35.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Welch and
McKiernan say
this is a step beyond what's
known as kangaroo

36:35.626 --> 36:40.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
care, the skin-to-skin contact
that's been
taught in many NICUs since the
1990s.

36:40.131 --> 36:43.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARY MCKIERNAN: I have been a
nurse here many
years, but there was something
missing.

36:43.601 --> 36:47.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what was missing was that
helping the
mother to get to that emotional
connection.

36:47.805 --> 36:52.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ELIA CARDENAS, Mother: Take care
of them for
me, St. Jude.

36:52.310 --> 36:56.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Getting past
her fear of
losing her babies has been one
of the biggest

36:56.881 --> 36:58.649 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
