working in
Chicago's schools.

53:20.197 --> 53:25.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says poetry's place in the
education of
young people is needed more than
ever.

53:25.101 --> 53:29.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUAN FELIPE HERRERA: We have got
to let our
students' lives, all their
lives, not just

53:29.873 --> 53:33.476 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
part of their lives, express
itself in as
many ways as possible.

53:33.510 --> 53:36.780 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And where else are they going to
get that
openness and freedom?

53:36.813 --> 53:38.848 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
In what other area in school?

53:38.882 --> 53:41.518 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Maybe there's other areas, but,
for sure,
poetry.

53:41.551 --> 53:45.555 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Herrera and
others involved
hope this project can be a model
for other

53:45.589 --> 53:47.390 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
cities around the nation.

53:47.424 --> 53:55.632 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Jeffrey Brown
